.TH GIT-PR-STACK 1 "2026-06-13" "git-tools" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
git-pr-stack \- discover a linear GitHub pull request stack
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git pr-stack
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ number|url|branch ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B git pr-stack
discovers the linear GitHub pull request stack connected to a target pull
request and prints it in parent-to-child order. Without a target, it uses the
pull request for the current branch.
.PP
A stack is connected when one pull request's base branch is another pull
request's head branch. If a stack branches into multiple child pull requests,
the command stops instead of guessing a landing order.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-porcelain
Print one stable tab-separated record per pull request for scripts.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show help.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Stack printed.
.TP
.B 1
Stack could not be read or is branched.
.TP
.B 2
Usage or local environment error.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-pr-ready (1),
.BR git-pr-restack (1),
.BR git-pr-land-stack (1)
